06/08/2003
ANKARA, Turkey -- The situation in Iraq and the transfer of the Turkish peacekeeping contingent there were discussed at a meeting of country's top state officials, chaired by Prime Minister Recep Tayyip Erdogan on Tuesday (5 August). Chief of the General Staff Gen Hilmi Ozkok, Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul, National Defence Minister Vecdi Gonul and Interior Minister Abdulkadir Aksu also took part in the meeting. Although the participants reached no concrete decision on the issue, they agreed that Turkey should join the international community's peacekeeping efforts in Iraq. (Anadolu Agency - 05/08/03)
